    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Thompson</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 30.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In connection with instruction No. 97, of
                    February 6 last, directing Mr. McCreery to make formal inquiry as to whether two
                    certain bonds issued by the Mexican Empire in 1864 are redeemable by the Mexican
                    treasury, I inclose herewith for your information a copy of a letter<note n="a"
                        xml:id="d234fna">Not printed.</note> from Mr. G. T. Moeskes, inclosing a
                    copy of correspondence which he has had since then with the Mexican treasury on
                    the subject.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
